57 "§13A-11-243
58 (a) Any law enforcement officer and any or agent of the
59 a county or the municipality appointed pursuant to Section
60 13A-11-242, having reasonable belief, evidence of, or having
61 found a dog or cat to be neglected or cruelly treated that has
62 a reasonable belief of, has evidence of, or observes a
63 violation of this article may perform do either of the
64 following:
65 (1) Remove the dog or cat from its present location.
66 (2) Order the owner of the dog or cat to provide
67 certain care to the dog or cat at the owner's expense without
68 the removal of the dog or cat from its present location.
69 (b) Neither the county or municipality, nor any
70 employee or agent of the county or municipality, acting in
71 good faith, shall be liable for any actions taken under this
72 section, regardless of whether or not the dog or cat is
73 returned to its owner after impoundment."
74 Section 2. Section 13A-11-241.1 is added to the Code of
75 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
76 §13A-11-241.1
77 (a) A person commits the crime of abandonment of a dog
78 or cat if he or she, with criminal negligence, abandons a dog
79 or cat.
80 (b) Abandonment of a dog or cat is a Class C
81 misdemeanor.
82 Section 3. This act shall become effective on October
83 1, 2026.
